Hampton Airfield was privately-owned, and was located 2 miles north of Hampton, New 
Hampshire. It was classified by the FAA as a non-towered public use airport. The airport 
elevation was 93 feet above mean sea level and there was one runway oriented in a 02/20 
configuration. Runway 02 was turf, and in good condition. The total length was 2,100 foot long 
by 170 foot wide.
